@startuml visited_flow
skinparam backgroundColor #1a1a2e
skinparam defaultFontColor #e0e0e0
skinparam defaultFontName "DejaVu Sans"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor #16213e
  BorderColor #6200EE
  FontColor #ffffff
  BorderThickness 2
}
skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor #16213e
  BorderColor #03DAC6
  FontColor #03DAC6
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color #03DAC6
  FontColor #e0e0e0
  FontSize 11
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #0f3460
  BorderColor #6200EE
  FontColor #ddd
}
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #6200EE

title <color:#ffffff><size:18>Visited Artworks — Full Logic Flow</size></color>

actor User
participant "ArtDetailScreen" as UI
participant "ArtViewModel" as VM
participant "VisitedRepository" as REPO
participant "Firestore DB" as FS
participant "ArtListScreen" as LIST

== 1. CHECK: Is artwork visited? ==

UI -> VM: LaunchedEffect(artworkId)\nloadVisitedStatus()
VM -> REPO: isVisited(artworkId)
REPO -> FS: GET document(artworkId)\n.get().await()
FS --> REPO: doc.exists() &&\ndoc["isVisited"] == true
REPO --> VM: Boolean
VM --> UI: update UI state\n(checkbox / button color)

== 2. MARK AS VISITED ==

User -> UI: Toggle "Mark as Visited"
UI -> VM: toggleVisited(artwork, isVisited=true)
VM -> REPO: addVisit(VisitedArtwork)
note over REPO
  Data copied from API response
  to avoid future API calls
end note
REPO -> FS: document(artworkId).set(visitedArtwork)
FS --> REPO: success
REPO --> VM: done
VM -> LIST: combinedArtState refreshed\nartwork.is_visited_local = true

== 3. REAL-TIME VISITED LIST ==

LIST -> VM: getVisitsFlow() (on screen open)
VM -> REPO: getVisitsFlow()
REPO -> FS: addSnapshotListener\non visited_artworks collection
note over FS
  Firestore pushes updates
  automatically on any change
end note
FS --> REPO: snapshot (new data)
REPO --> VM: callbackFlow { trySend(items) }
VM --> LIST: visitedList StateFlow\nupdated instantly

== 4. REMOVE VISIT ==

User -> UI: Uncheck "Mark as Visited"
UI -> VM: toggleVisited(artwork, isVisited=false)
VM -> REPO: setVisitedStatus(artworkId, false)
REPO -> FS: document(artworkId).update("isVisited", false)
VM -> REPO: removeVisitIfNoPhotos(artworkId)
note over REPO
  If isVisited=false AND
  imageUrls is empty →
  delete document entirely
end note
REPO -> FS: document(artworkId).delete()

== 5. VIEW OTHER USERS' VISITS ==

UI -> VM: loadPublicVisits(artworkId)
VM -> REPO: getPublicVisitsForArtwork(artworkId)
REPO -> FS: collectionGroup("visited_artworks")\n.whereEqualTo("id", artworkId)
note over FS
  collectionGroup queries
  ALL users' sub-collections
  at once
end note
FS --> REPO: List<VisitedArtwork>\n(from all users)
REPO --> VM: publicVisits
VM --> UI: show community photos

@enduml
